narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Developed my musicianship skills (ear training, sight singing etc)
Sight reading, rhythm, metric space, harmonic and rhythmic dictation. Tonal and atonal harmony.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: Michael is an excellent instructor, very knowledgable and changed how I listened to music. Weaknesses: more work than I was expecting from a half credit course.

The course was heavier on theory than I expected... I thought this class would focus more on skill-building since there are companion intro music classes to this one that focus solely on theory (MUSI 210/211).

Overall, the course was good. However, at times, assignments felt too difficult for the level of the course and required much outside time and help. If more of the assigned creative/out-of-the-box questions that had less directly to do with the course were delegated to be extra credit, homeworks would have been more manageable.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, it helps but you never know how it will turn out because it depends a whole lot on who the teacher happens to be
